  <data name="textBox1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>This timer is very inaccurate, it may trigger when it shouldn't or it may not trigger when it should. You should not completely rely on it. Until alignment logging in-game is fixed, this is the best that can be done.

You can use "verify" button to check, which log messages caused the timer in the last 30 minutes. Even that is not 100% reliable because some events are not yet tracked. (list below)

This is what should be tracked correctly (unless bugged):
&gt;Butchering a human corpse (- 1)
&gt;Burying a human corpse (+ 2)
&gt;Listening to a confession (+/- 1)
&gt;Confessing to a priest (+/- 5)
&gt;Holding a sermon (+/- 1)
&gt;Listening to a sermon (up to +/- 4)
&gt;Fo special: plant a sprout or a flower (+ 1)
&gt;Magranon special: mine (+ 0.5)

This is what will sometimes give false positives:
&gt;Vynora special: cutting down an old, very old or overaged tree (+ 1) &gt;&gt; triggers for any tree regardless age
&gt;Magranon special: kill a creature (+ 0.5) &gt;&gt; triggers for any creature killed around, may work on killing players (needs test)
&gt;Libila special: kill a creature (- 0.5) &gt;&gt; works for any creature killed around, may work on killing players (needs test)
&gt;Healing someone else (+ 1) &gt;&gt; no info who is being healed, false positives for healing yourself

This is what may be added in future in some form:
&gt;Converting someone to your religion (+/- 1)
&gt;Successful Lockpicking (-5)
&gt;Casting Bless on players (seems random). (+ 1)
&gt;Sacrificing items in an altar (at least worth 50c get price) (+/- 1)
&gt;Praying at the White Light on the Wild server. (+ 3)
&gt;Praying at the Black Light on the Wild server. (- 3)
&gt;Desecrating an altar (- 2)
&gt;Vynora special: working on walls (+ 0.5)
&gt;Killing of a whitelighter (- 5) &gt;&gt; missing log messages for killing players, would trigger for all players
&gt;Killing of a blacklighter (+ 5) &gt;&gt; missing log messages for killing players, would trigger for all players</value>
